arms.";i:32;s:39:"This should stretch out the piriformis.";i:33;s:53:"Bring your knee towards your chest using your arm to.";i:34;s:33:"This stretch is good for posture.";i:35;s:48:"Sit upright and away from the back of the chair.";i:36;s:34:"Pull your shoulders back and down.";i:37;s:33:"Extend your arms out to the side.";i:38;s:81:"Gently push your chest forward and up until you feel a stretch across your chest.";i:39;s:44:"Hold for 5 to 10 seconds and repeat 5 times.";i:40;s:46:"Try these warm-up chair exercises for seniors.";i:41;s:94:"Sit up straight and slowly tilt your head toward your right shoulder until you feel a stretch.";i:42;s:80:"Hold this position while gradually extending your left arm down and to the side.";i:43;s:56:"You should feel a stretch on the left side of your neck.";i:44;s:134:"New infographic created by a power wheelchair company KD Smart Chair visualizes the best 13 stretching exercises for wheelchair users.";i:45;s:96:"Sitting long hours in a wheelchair may cause back pains stress joint discomfort muscle tensions.";i:46;s:103:"Sitting too long in a wheelchair may lead to lower back pain and tightening of back muscles and joints.";i:47;s:48:"Under those circumstances doing some stretching.";i:48;s:75:"Sit comfortably at the edge of the chair without feeling like falling over.";i:49;s:57:"Keep the back straight and the core abs and lumbar tight.";i:50;s:76:"Place both hands at the sides of the chair and grip the seat to keep stable.";i:51;s:72:"Place both feet far out in front of the body and point the toes forward.";i:52;s:95:"Seated in a chair with good posture hold a ball with both hands slightly in front of your body.";i:53;s:123:"Squeeze the ball to activate the finger joints then slowly press the ball with both hands as if trying to deflate the ball.";i:54;s:38:"Hold for 4 seconds and slowly release.";i:55;s:22:"Repeat the exercise 8.";i:56;s:71:"This stretch is also known as the rhomboid upper or upper back stretch.";i:57;s:76:"Clasp your hands in front of you and lower your head in line with your arms.";i:58;s:44:"Press forward and hold for 10 to 30 seconds.";i:59;s:15:"Desk Stretch 8.";i:60;s:70:"Relieve the tension in your hips and glutes with this seated exercise.";i:61;s:113:"Sitting straight in your chair with your left foot on the ground cross your right ankle on top of your left knee.";i:62;s:72:"Keeping your back straight gently lean forward until you feel a stretch.";i:63;s:90:"Place an exercise band around the back of your wheelchair and hold the ends in your hands.";i:64;s:35:"Sit tall in your starting position.";i:65;s:91:"Extend your arms out in front of you with your palms down as far as you can go comfortably.";i:66;s:67:"Sit tall in a chair and extend straight arms up inhaling as you go.";i:67;s:87:"As you exhale twist your torso to the left and place your right hand on your left knee.";i:68;s:67:"Reach your left arm behind you placing it on the back of the chair.";i:69;s:115:"Breathe in deeply getting longer through the spine and as you exhale see if you can increase the twist more gently.";i:70;s:38:"Sit up tall in your chair or stand up.";i:71;s:54:"Stretch your arms overhead and interlock your fingers.";i:72;s:94:"Turn the palms to the ceiling as you lift your chin up tilt your head back and gaze up at the.";i:73;s:89:"Chair based exercises will develop your cardio fitness muscular strength and flexibility.";i:74;s:54:"Here are some of the best chair exercises for seniors.";i:75;s:116:"Practice these basic movements and choose one or two exercises from each category for a well-rounded seated workout.";i:76;s:24:"Warm Up Chair Exercises.";i:77;s:162:"Aerobic exercise stretches and strengthens the muscles that support your low back which combined with healthy eating can also help you maintain your ideal weight.";i:78;s:74:"If youre overweight the extra pounds add to the strain on your lower back.";i:79;s:55:"Aerobic exercise like walking can help you lose weight.";i:80;s:26:"Office Chair Back Stretch.";i:81;s:76:"While sitting reach both hands behind your back and around the office chair.";i:82;s:68:"One you have a good hold arch your back and move your chest forward.";i:83;s:52:"Hold each stretch for 30 seconds and repeat 5 times.";i:84;s:18:"Reach for the Sky.";i:85;s:83:"To stretch your back interlock both hands above your head palms facing the ceiling.";i:86;s:152:"2 Chair-based flexibility exercises What this guide is about Flexibility exercises or stretches are used to improve your range of motion at your joints.";i:87;s:150:"A healthy functional range of movement is important for everyday life - for example reaching overhead for something on a shelf or putting on a jacket.";}}